# Shell scripts must always check out with LF line endings, regardless of
# a contributor's local core.autocrlf setting -- a CRLF shebang line
# (#!/usr/bin/env bash\r) fails outright on Linux/Mac with "bash\r: No such
# file or directory", which would silently break these scripts for anyone
# who clones on Windows and runs them on the actual deploy target.
*.sh text eol=lf
